! SECURITY NOTE, plaintext secrets in a TFTP'd config, accepted threat model.
! This file is served unauthenticated over TFTP on the management network and
! it carries:
!   * `enable secret 5 ...`            (line ~45, type 5 salted MD5)
!   * `username admin secret 5 ...`    (line ~50, type 5 salted MD5)
!   * `snmp-server community GLITCHED-RO RO 1`  (line ~126, plaintext community)
! The operator accepts this exposure under the following threat model,
!   * The TFTP file is reachable only from the management VLAN, which is not
!     routed to participant networks.
!   * External SNMP access against the deployed switches is read only and
!     gated by `ip access-list standard 1` (line ~113), only the internal
!     server subnet `92.33.56.32/27` (line ~115) can poll.
!   * SSH/management access is gated by `access-class ipv4-management`
!     (line ~141) bound to vty 0 15, only the jumpgate at `92.33.56.4`
